---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Group Scout" description="What Group Scout is, the problem it solves, and how it works">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto py-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100 mb-8">About Group Scout</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <p>
        Group Scout is a Go-based pipeline that monitors public data for hotel group sales
        leads—construction projects, contract awards, film productions, and sports events. It
        presents actionable intelligence to a sales team via Slack.
      </p>

      <p>
        The problem: hotel group sales requires proactive outreach.
        Signals that predict room blocks exist in public data—building permits, contract
        awards, and permit filings—but are scattered and inconsistent.
        Group Scout automates collection, deduplication, enrichment, and delivery.
      </p>

      <p>
        The stack: Go backend with a Postgres datastore, Claude for structured enrichment,
        and a Slack Block Kit digest for delivery. Data sources include municipal
        building permits and contract awards. The pipeline runs on a schedule and posts only
        new leads above a configurable threshold.
      </p>

      <p>
        This site contains two blogs. The <a href="/blog/">build log</a> records the product journey:
        decisions, failures, and domain knowledge.
        The <a href="/engineering/">engineering notes</a> examine technical implementations:
        architecture, data models, Go patterns, and LLM integration.
      </p>

      <p>
        The source code is at <a href="https://github.com/alvindcastro/groupscout">github.com/alvindcastro/groupscout</a>.
        To learn about the developer, visit <a href="https://alvindcastro.github.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">alvindcastro.github.io</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
